                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1106.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-23T11:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 20, 12 midnight. Held a conference tonight with Provisional Government
                    Cabinet and was informed that there is no hope present Congress will approve
                    financial relief of any kind, its hope being to defeat Government by starvation;
                    neither has Minister of Finance any further plan to advance unless you decide to
                    place funds already appropriated for Public Works in this country. Government is
                    proceeding with rigor against Arias which may result in outbreak in the north.
                    Arias resorting with Rosselean, Haitian brigand. I fear that our failure to
                    furnish financial assistance now will permit reform in financial comptroller to
                    slip from our hands. This expectation relief is absolutely essential to our
                    maintaining a consistent successful policy and without same the Government faces
                    supreme difficulties in maintaining orderly procedure on election days. I am
                    promised at tonight’s meeting the Government will exert every effort for honest
                    poll.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
